        "title": "feat(ui): per-agent ElevenLabs Voice/TTS settings in control-ui",
        "body": "## feat(ui): per-agent ElevenLabs Voice/TTS settings in control-ui\n\nAdds a Voice/TTS card to the agent overview tab for per-agent ElevenLabs TTS config.\n\n### ClawSweeper P1/P2 review findings addressed (commit f11953619e)\n\n**[P1] SecretRef-backed TTS API keys preserved**\nAdded `isSecretRefObject()` helper. `resolveAgentTts` now detects SecretRef objects at `providers.elevenlabs.apiKey` and sets `apiKeyIsSecretRef: true`. The template renders a disabled read-only field instead of casting to string. Existing SecretRef-backed credentials are safe.\n\n**[P2] Runtime TTS config resolution mirrors runtime contract**\n`resolveAgentTts` now starts from `messages.tts` as the base layer and deep-merges per-agent defaults and entry overrides — matching `resolveEffectiveTtsConfig` in `src/tts/tts-config.ts`. Valid global TTS configs no longer appear disabled.\n\n**[P2] ElevenLabs modelId write path corrected**\nHandler path changed `providers.elevenlabs.model` -> `providers.elevenlabs.modelId`, matching the field the ElevenLabs speech provider reads for synthesis. `resolveAgentTts` reads `modelId` first, falls back to `model` for compat.\n\n### Tests\n- 10/10 agent unit tests pass (incl. new SecretRef read-only test)\n- 11/11 i18n structural alignment tests pass\n- Build clean",
